lgp.core.program

Class ProgramGenerator<TProgram,TOutput extends Output<TProgram>>

  • lgp.core.program.ProgramGenerator<TProgram,TOutput>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Module
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BaseProgramGenerator

    public class ProgramGenerator<TProgram,TOutput extends Output<TProgram>>
implements Module

    Generates class Program instances to be used in an LGP population.

    The implementation is done as a module, allowing for custom generation logic for programs to be defined. The only requirement is that calls to the ProgramGenerator.next method returns a sequence of program samples.

    An implementation is expected to provide an class Environment, in order to provide access to any component loaded into the the LGP environment, as well as an class InstructionGenerator. Instruction generators themselves are modules, so each can be defined as a module.

    See Also:
    class Program, ProgramGenerator.next, class Environment, class InstructionGenerator
